TAYLOR
v.
WAKE COUNTY 93P18-2 Supreme Court of North Carolina. January 30, 2019 Harvey L. Kennedy, Attorney at Law, Harold L. Kennedy, III, Attorney at Law, Winston-Salem, Donna M. Taylor, Attorney at Law, Pilot Mountain, for Taylor, LaTonya A. Roger A. Askew, Senior Deputy County Attorney, Jennifer M. Jones, Senior Assistant County Attorney, for Wake County, d/b/a the Division of Social Services.

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 11th of December 2018 by Defendant to Strike Motion for Reconsideration:

"Motion Dismissed as moot by order of the Court in conference, this the 30th of January 2019."
